                    Adelaide

          A Code Editor, but for Android.

Adelaide is a lightweight code editor designed for Android devices.

The goal is to provide a fast, clean editing experience without unnecessary
features or complexity. Adelaide focuses on the essentials needed for viewing
and editing source code on mobile devices.

Planned Features

- Open and edit local files.
- Syntax highlighting for supported languages.
- Simple search and replace within the current file and whole codebase

Goals

- Fast startup and smooth performance.
- Simple, touch-friendly interface.
- Minimal resource usage.
- Reliable editing experience.
- Clean and fit Mobile UI/UX

Status

Adelaide is currently just a concept idea, and will not be worked on at all
until AsterIDE v2.0.0 is stable, after this, we will work on making an
Android code editor, for those who don't like Ads.